/*
:name: latch_active_low
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: latch_active_low.llow8
:pyrope_top: llow8
*/

// FIXME tracker for todo/livehd/2f-latch (M1, M2). A transparent-LOW latch: Q
// follows D while the gate is 0 and holds while it is 1. This is the master half
// of every master/slave pair and the enable latch of every ICG, so its polarity
// must survive end to end.
//
// Today polarity is NOT carried by the Latch cell's `posclk` pin on the
// Pyrope/slang path — it is baked into the enable cone (`enable = !clk`), and
// `posclk` is only ever written by the yosys $dlatch importer. 2f-latch M2 makes
// `posclk` authoritative and cross-checks it against the enable cone; a
// disagreement between the two is the "posclk double-negation" miscompile that a
// symmetric before/after gate cannot see (hence the cross-model gating rule).
// PROMOTE when M2 lands.
pub comb llow8(clk:bool, d:u8) -> (q:u8) {
  reg l:u8:[latch=true]
  if !clk {
    l = d
  }
  q = l
}
